<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, I posted in the enchanter forum when the change to dire charm, well, actually how exp is earned using a DC pet was implemented in the last patch and got so many replies about how it wasn't a nerf. <P>So, I've been thinking. There must have been something in VI's logic, to say to themselves, that it wasn't fair for enchanters to earn exp with this ability at a rate that must have been to high for justification.<P>So, here's my idea to even the playing field for those who find quad kiting for exp and whats left of the AE'ers out there, to have an unacceptable advantage over other classes in the ability to gain exp.<P>VI should make it so that EXP gained in the same killing blast should yield less and less exp. <P>For example, many druids and wizards are very efficient quad kiters, but why should they get an exp advantage that all other classes can't enjoy, so make it such that, sure, they get full exp on the first exp message, but maybe only 75% on second, 50% on the third and 25% on the last. As for AE, anything after the 4th kill you get ZERO exp thereafter.<P>Now I know that everyone, except for maybe those effected naturally, would love to see this implemented to even the playing field or perhaps, make it a disadvantagious strategy so as to free up areas in the game that are basically unplayable because of those that use these tactics in their game play. I mean how times has your game play been upset because of a quad or AE pull gone bad?<P>Either way, you will HAVE to know this is not a NERF to your abilities. Your snare will still work as before, your AE spells will still do the damage or stun as they did before, this is just an attempt to even the playing field for all those other classes that can't employ those tactics for exp gain. <P>Just as it was necessary to increase the penalty to enchanters, that after 60 levels and a minimum of 27 AA points got when they got dire charm and it was somehow found to be unbalancing for use for exp gain.<P>So everyone please let VI know that we only want a level playing field and to those who may not like this idea, we are not calling for a NERF in any of your abilities.<P>Anyway, just wanted to share this out front in the general forum and not buried back on the enchanter forum where you all may not get a chance to comment on it. Here's to a more equal and safer playing field - cheers!<P>--------------------<P>Bezze Beezz - 60 Enchanter<BR>Willowglade - 51 Druid<BR>Kempheren - 49 Warrior<BR>Taffey Meltaway - 48 Paladin (Gnome - yea baby!)<BR>Diller Dahde - 38 Cleric<BR>Rosebird Icywing - 34 Wizard<BR>Todfeind - 28 Necro<BR>Zypper - 19 SK (Gnome of course!)<BR>Fennin Ro
</FONT>
