<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
As an enchanter with Dire Charm, I agree with one point: It wasn't nerfed.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> <P>I find (and so does EVERY person I've grouped with since) that Dire Charm is still more sufficient than a conventional charmed pet. With the mana sinks (enc/clr) and time consuming of keeping a mob charmed (when you could be pulling instead), it evens out. <P>Conventional charm tends to go in streaks. The bad ones are like this:<P>Mob breaks.<BR>AE Stun .<BR>Root (resist!).<BR>Pounded on.<BR>Root.<BR>Charm lands but breaks in 5 seconds.<BR>Cleric/Druid/Shammy heals.<BR>AE Stun.<BR>Charm resist. More pounding.<BR>More Cleric heals.<BR>Charm lands.<BR>Charm breaks just as a three-pull comes in.<BR>Pet is hasted and duel wielding, and three other mobs in camp.<BR>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<P>Uhh yes, you get the picture. With Dire Charm, pet's not gonna break. I can pull for groups steadily. Cleric is almost always FM and is actually nuking.<P>So Bezze you're right! Dire Charm was not nerfed.<P>While we're "not nerfing" classes, let's penalize soloing monks by 50% if they use Mend. And those damn Paladins by 75% if they use LoH. And penalize Necros by 60% if they use any type of Fear spell. Uhhhhh yeah! Let's send this to Verant right now.
</FONT>
