Curley,<P>"The game begins at 51", you say? Well, maybe, but you still need to plow through 50 levels to get there, don't you? And the extra experience gained through quadding makes this happen quicker, thus giving those quadding characters an advantage over those of us who can only handle one, MAYBE two critters.<P>A quadding druid has the same downtime as anyone else taking down one - probably less, because he didn't take much, if any damage. There's no "medding 4 times as long". <P>Think about it, if it didn't give an advantage to the quadding wizard / druid... would they do it? I sure as heck wouldn't want four things chasing me around if it didn't give me some very nice benifets, such as 4x exp and 4x loot.<P>And as for quadding and other players... Maybe you've never been the victim of a quad train? Maybe you've never gone to a decent zone only to find that all the mobs there are running around in a circle after some Keebler elf? Quadding hinders other players. Go to Cobalt Scar to get some exp while trying to pick up some hides for  y guildies and gems for myself? All being quadded. This causes me time (getting to Cobalt Scar), experience (being unable to get a single kill there) and money (not being able to loot any of these things, and then having to buy what I'm looking for from a quadder).
