<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Hyena Shaman:<BR><STRONG>Curley,<BR>"The game begins at 51", you say? Well, maybe, but you still need to plow through 50 levels to get there, don't you? And the extra experience gained through quadding makes this happen quicker, thus giving those quadding characters an advantage over those of us who can only handle one, MAYBE two critters.<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Shaman are some of the best soloers in the game.  You will likely get far more exp per hour than my druid.  Nevertheless, yes, quadding is definitely a way for a druid (and wizards, lets not forget the wizards) to get good experience solo.  It also has severe limitations.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Hyena Shaman:<BR><STRONG>A quadding druid has the same downtime as anyone else taking down one - probably less, because he didn't take much, if any damage. There's no "medding 4 times as long". <BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Wrong.  A quadding druid has more downtime than someone taking down one.  When I quad kite, unless I can get clarity, you know what I do?<P>I quad.  Then I find a nice place to hide, and then I go do house work for 15 minutes, because that's about how long it takes to get a full bar of mana, rebuff, and go quad again.<P>Quadding is faster than regular exp grouping, but not that much.<P>Don't kid yourself.  Notice how most areas still have druids shouting for group?  Wonder why?  Why aren't they all quad kiting if its 4 times the experience and loot?  hmmm...<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Hyena Shaman:<BR><STRONG>Think about it, if it didn't give an advantage to the quadding wizard / druid... would they do it? I sure as heck wouldn't want four things chasing me around if it didn't give me some very nice benifets, such as 4x exp and 4x loot.<BR></STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>It takes about as much mana to kill 4 as it does to kill 2, if you are smart.  So you might as well kill 4, then med for a long time, as kill 1 at a time and still med for a long time after about the 3rd kill.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Hyena Shaman:<BR><STRONG>And as for quadding and other players... Maybe you've never been the victim of a quad train? Maybe you've never gone to a decent zone only to find that all the mobs there are running around in a circle after some Keebler elf? Quadding hinders other players. Go to Cobalt Scar to get some exp while trying to pick up some hides for  y guildies and gems for myself? All being quadded. This causes me time (getting to Cobalt Scar), experience (being unable to get a single kill there) and money (not being able to loot any of these things, and then having to buy what I'm looking for from a quadder).</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>So you went to the one zone in the game that is very deliberately laid out for quad kiting and were suprised there were quadders there?  The mobs are spread out.  If you have the faction to go there, the mobs don't aggro.  There's a nice long "runway" to pull down.  Its perfectly set up for quadding.<P>And take a look next time.  Its not some "keebler elf" half the time, its a wizard.  That's right.  Wizards quad too, and about half the people in CS are wizards.<P>I do agree however that quadding is a great way to get through the low 50s.  I spent 52 and 53 in CS, and part of 54, but the exp was getting too slow.  And it was mostly because either I didn't have the time to go find a group (I play in chunks of as little as 30 minutes sometimes) or because when I did try and find a group I got essentially "nah you're not a cleric, we don't want you".  So I quadded a lot.<P>Was it fun and exciting, was it massive experience?  It was decent experience, and it was boring as hell.  I only did it because I wanted my next spell level.  Now my druid is shelved because I was soooo bored with it.<P>The grass is always greener eh?<P>--------------------<P>54 Druid<BR>52 Warrior<BR>50 Ranger<BR>44 Cleric<BR>And one of everything else in the 20s and 30s scampering about the lands of Norrath.
