Ok...speaking from the role of a druid who spent 90% of his time soloing until lvl 54. most druids cannot quad efficiantly until 34 and lightning strike ( imo ).<P>yes it is faster xp to quad then in a group, but it is much more dangerous and loot generally isnt as good...here is why.<P>we can only quad outdoors. alot of the good quading areas, Tim Deep and such arent very frequented by clerics, and mobs can hit for up to 300 dmg ( spiroc BS ). death is easy if a couple break snare, or a little lag, or falling asleep...very few outdoor zones have good loot drops in the form of items and armor.<P>you dont want druids to be able to kite? hell i can still do root/dot and kill 3 mobs, maybe 4 with a full mana bar. its just a different strategy which works just as well. <P>face it...some classes will level much faster then others!! necros are just as good as druids with soloing...and even better post 54. why not nerf them? why not nerf the fungi so it cant be worn after 50?<P>also, at least on my server, i cant get a pick-up group to save me ass at 54. druids kinda suck post 50. so while it took us longer to get there, there was nothing in the end.<P>--------------------<P>Tyfin | Galat
