<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Bezze:<BR><STRONG>Sigh - sorry Lumine, was writing as you posted, but the fact of the matter is, the way a DC pets accounts for damage, unless your group size starts to be in the 5 or 6 member range, the pet will ALWAYS out damage the group. Well, unless your one of those uber duo's like MR. ICG can come up with, so no matter what, you are getting 50% or less of the exp a normal group would killing the same MOBs ... </STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Sorry if it seems like I'm dragging this out, but regardless of how much damage the pet does, you (the group) will never get less than 50% of the exp if you do ANY damage.  To say that you will get 50% OR LESS is just not the case.  Even VI said so in their release - if you do any damage, the DC pet "will never take more experience than it used to."  "Used to", in this case, means pre-patch, which was 50%.<P>VI clarified this a couple of times in follow-ups - here's the details from Rich Waters:<P><I>Situation 3 - You are soloing and you have a Dire Charmed pet<P>If you do half of the damage to the monster or more, you get all of the experience. <BR>If you do less than half of the damage to the monster, the pet gets between 25% and 50% of the experience, depending on how much damage it did. <BR>If you don't do any damage to the monster, the pet gets 75% of the experience. <P>Situation 4 - You are in a group and you have a Dire Charmed pet<P>If you or your group do half of the damage to the monster or more, your group gets all of the experience. <BR>If you or your group do less than half of the damage to the monster, the pet gets between 25% and 50% of the experience, depending on how much damage it did. <BR>If you or your group don't do any damage to the monster, the pet gets 75% of the experience. </I><P>So you and a Druid run off, grab a 8000hp DISPOSABLE tank, and commence to whuppin' butt.  You dot, the druid dots, and say the net is that the "tank" takes 40% of the exp.  This is still better than dragging a tank/cleric along, as they'll take 50%.  Add a shammie and you and the druid split 40%, rather than 60%.<P>If you already have a full group and DC pets are outdamaging the group, then either back the pet off when the mob is at 50% or back the pet off at 10% and blur.  Just like we always do.  What's so difficult about that?<P>Lumine
</FONT>
