Bezze, you're an idiot.<P>   <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><BR>However, let me say again, this post is not about DC pets or how they work, but for looking to change how exp is accounted for for "quad'ers" and AE'ers to level the playing field for all exp'ers and of course to make those zones, where it's employed, safer and more fun for everyone.<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>So you're saying, that Wizards and druids should be nerfed because "other" classes can't gain exp as "easily" as these two. Sounds like a classic case of class envy. <P>If quad kiting and ae grouping is nerfed, then you better come up with some way for wizards and druids getting in a group. Until level 60, I almost never got group invites. I don't have a bad reputation, but I could sit in classic pickup zones (you name it, I've tried em) and never get an invite. If you did a /who LFG, I've often seen wizards LFG the most. However, this is all coming from a chanter, probably one of the most desirable grouping characters, just short of the cleric. Why does this not surprise me?<P>In a standard exp situation, most groups choose druids first, wizards second. Why? Druids can backup heal, more efficient single target snare, buff, debuff, succor/evac, 2nd / 3rd best DDs, rains, ae spells etc. Wizards don't have any of that, short of evacs, dds (rains, aes) and an inefficient ae snare (ae = bad in alot of situations).<P>Also, quad kiting and ae grouping has VERY STRICT requirements, you can't just quad anywhere. You need melee only mobs, if they cast any form of spells, then it won't work. Has to be an outside zone as well, indoor quad kiting will not work (lack of room to move about, no sow or jboots etc). For ae grouping, you need specific mobs, eg mobs with "average" hitpoints, low resists, mobs that CAN be stunned, non rooted etc. There are very few good ae grouping zones left in the game now.<P>--------------------<P>Baron Holmium El`Blastee - 60 Erudite Wiz<BR>Roughin Tumble - 22 Vah Shir Beastlord<BR>Rhenhium - 21 Half Elf Bard<BR>Scandium - 30 Iksar Monk<BR>Tellurium - 14 Erudite Necromancer<BR>Torvonnilous
