<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have been away from these boards for some time, mostly due to the fact that i'd rather be in norath. This thread ...well, i could not pass this.<P>First, let me say I got dire charm the moment i got level 59. I'm sure ill get flamed by someone for not getting 60 first...<BR>so be it. The point is, I have what i would consider unique perspective on dire charm, since i have been using it for a verry long time now. I say here and now, yes, it HAS been nerfed. I'm sure, someone will come along and insist that it hasnt. Now, before someone comes and asks for "proof" ,let me explain how i have come to this conclusion.<P>     I have a tendency to to camp sebilis,<BR>near the pyra area. For those who arent familiar with that terminology, it means the area from the bridge to the entrance to the crypt camp. This (at least on the server I play on) is a closed camp. I.E. fixed amount of mobs from there per hour. I have been duoing this camp with the same 60 paladin, whenever im there, and the same BOK knight,<BR>not most of the time, but EVERY time. The BOK is a 125 hitter, every time. In other words, nothing has changed at all, in how we duo this area, other than pet changes. I can say with absolute certainty, that EXP after pet changes is noticeably and significantly less than it was before patch. Nooone and nothing will convince me otherwise, since this isnt something I suspect, but something I know for fact. How much different you ask?  Consistently, 2/3 of what it used to be, at best. That is, best case scenario, two thirds of the exp it it was pre patch. Worst case scenario, slightly less than half of what it used to be. No, I dont memblur near death, nor should I have to, nor will I.<P>Bezze is pissed that it was nerfed, as we all should be. He has been ridiculed by many of you (as im sure i will be) because hes not the type of person who "takes broken eggs and makes omlettes" , and instead calls them what they are. Broken eggs.<P> The point he's making in a round about way is:<BR>     If the changes to dire aren't a nerf, then it wouldnt be a nerf to make those same types of changes to AE/quadders. <P>I'm gonna go out on a limb and say that at least some of you understand this logic.<P> There seems to be alot of doublestandard floating in this thread. What is a nerf...what isnt a nerf...how some think these changes weren't a nerf, yet apply those changes to quadders/AE groups, all the sudden it is a nerf now, and everyone is attacking Bezze for calling for a nerf.<BR>The doublestandard there is sickening.<P>Now, on to some interesting quotes from this thread:<P>Quote: ICG<P>" I find (and so does EVERY person I've grouped with since) that Dire Charm is still more sufficient than a conventional charmed pet." <P>Duh, it was before the patch.<P>Quote:Bezze<P>"If you and EVERY person you play with think that losing so much exp for using your DC pet is acceptable, then all I can say is you have very low expectations of what is acceptable, ie. the previous rate was a 50/50 split (which was, as well, unacceptable to me btw, as it was with most other people who used pets, charmed or otherwise). "<P>About damn time someone said it. The word is unacceptable. There is no logic, no argument,<BR>no jedi mind trick , or otherwise, that can justify pets taking any EXP at all, ever. Not untill such time as nukes and weapons take exp as well. Maybe heals should suffer an exp suck as well.<P>Quote: ICG<BR>(gotta say, this is one of my fav's )<P>"Bezze: Try to get this through that thick head of yours. EXP COMES FASTER WITH DC! I have tried both ways. Even DUOING, it comes FASTER and STEADILY."<P><BR>Comes faster with DC than??? Without a pet?<BR>DUH. Even duoing you've tried it both ways?<BR>You keep saying it comes faster, faster than what? Something i thought was obvious to everyone, EXP will always come faster with a DC pet in a duo, than with none.<P>Quote:ICG <P>"EIGHT blues of AA exp last night in a two and a half hour block duoing with a 60th level Warrior. That warrior seemed satisfied with the exp he was getting. "<P><BR>Guess your not getting that good of exp duoing with your 60'th level friend, since before patch, I was getting 1 full point every 4 hours duoing with my paladin friend,<BR>now getting about two thirds of a point<BR>in the same 4 hour stint in the same camp with the same pet duoing with the same person. Heh, and on a side note, your warrior buddy was satisfied he was getting permabuffed by you, not just at the exp.<BR>Like any warrior would complain about slow exp while he was hasted and haveing fun doing his thing.../boggle<P>Quote: ICG<P>"My clerics don't usually make nukes. I keep pulls coming steadily so there are no less than two mobs in camp at once. I don't know where you waste time grouping Bezze, but I don't screw around in the low level spider camps in Velketor, or the first few camps in Sebilis. Pulls come in, the MT takes aggro of adds until they're mezzed. So yes, my clerics are mainly healing. "<P>Callin it as i see it, if you're killing slowly enough in a camp that actually has a DC'able mob near it, that your tanks are taking that much damage to warrant heals,<BR>your're doing sometyhing wrong. For the most part, if you have well equipped tanks (understand i mean WELL equipped, with gear better than what can be bought in /auction)<BR>you dont need a cleric. Flame away all ya like, but its a fact. Speedy killing negates the need for a cleric, because it negates the time it takes for tanks to be damaged enough to warrant heals of anything more than shaman/druid caliber. Not my opinion, but fact.<P>Quote: Sundevil.<BR>(another one of my favorites)<P>"Some would argue that the ability of other classes to walk into a zone and get a group within five minutes is an exp advantage"<P>I have to assume thats a shot at chanters,<BR>and i have to assume thats a mage or wiz saying it. Hmmm, what about the two to 4 melee in every group vs maybe, and i do mean MAYBE 1 chanter in each group. That ease of getting a group argument is ...well, stale, unless you're going to bounce it off melee as well, and quit singleing out chanters.<P>Quote:Tyfin.<P>"also, at least on my server, i cant get a pick-up group to save me ass at 54. druids kinda suck post 50. so while it took us longer to get there, there was nothing in the end"<P>Not singleing out the poster of this particular nugget for anything other than to ask 1 question. Whats in the end for chanters? Do you really have it so bad as a druid?<P>Quote: Lumine-Jaz (who is quoting VI)<P>"n most situations (with an active party, for example) the Dire Charmed pet will not take experience. Like all pets, they will take 75% of the experience if no PC does damage to the target. As long as a player does damage to a creature, a Dire Charmed pet will never take more experience than it used to."<P><BR>First, casted pets NEVER take more than 50 % exp, no matter what. So the "Like all pets, they will take 75% of the experience if no PC does damage to the target" part is flat out wrong.<P>Second, "As long as a player does damage to a creature, a Dire Charmed pet will never take more experience than it used to."<P>Key words being ""As long as a player does damage to a creature".  Like so many mages and people on this board insist, chanters aren't nukers, so this was a direct assault on chanter solo exp. think anything else, and your ...well...lieing to yourself.<BR>I know you keep referring to what VI themselves have said, but can anyone on this board believe them, or trust that what they're saying is truth? I didnt think so.<P>Quote:Friss<P>"A twink melee can lvl faster then any other class, and a lvl 60 melee can solo for AA points faster then casters can. The only time a melee can be beaten are in AE groups, and even then most groups have 1 melee in it."<P>This couldn't be more true.<P>Quote:Jezzie<P>"There is no good reason to nerf quad-kiting"<P>Heh, you're probably right, but there was no reason to levy a penalty on dire charm, or any pet penaltys at all for that matter.<P>Quote: Senalin<BR>"people should be free to expermient with the abilities given to them and get away from the "holy trinity" veiw of grouping...that gets boring after awhile."<P>Absolutely. However, nerfs like the one to DC, don't foster that happening.<P><BR>Quote:Bezze<P>"Unless one has a chance to see it for themselves and not be blinded by the "wow factor" does it sink in that your losing exp for no good reason. "<P>I couldn't agree more. The wow factor disapears fast when you can't find a pet, and wait an hour plus, so your DC isnt wasted on a sub par pet.(sub par meaning <BR>less than the best you can get for where you are)<BR>Every pet class is losing EXP for no good reason. Every single one.<P>To makes this short and sweet: <P>What was done to DC either was or wasnt a nerf. If it was, then we all ought to be angry. If it wasnt, don't ***** when someone <BR>else says to apply those changes to you and your class. Don't be a hypocrit and say on one hand that DC wasn't nerfed, then turn around and say applying those exp modifiers <BR>to quadding and AE groups would be a nerf.<P>--------------------<P>Master Adryk Storm<P>Prophecy<P>Bertoxx
