<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Adryk Storm:<BR><STRONG>What was done to DC either was or wasnt a nerf. If it was, then we all ought to be angry. If it wasnt, don't ***** when someone <BR>else says to apply those changes to you and your class. Don't be a hypocrit and say on one hand that DC wasn't nerfed, then turn around and say applying those exp modifiers <BR>to quadding and AE groups would be a nerf.</STRONG><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>So you agree that it isn't hypocritical when I say that the change to DC was a nerf but that it's flat out stupid to ask that something else be nerfed in turn to make up for it?<P>Just about every class gets something nerfed to some degree at some time or another.  Disease Cloud for shadow knights lost its taunt component (to say nothing of the nerfs to the CoS or the Coterie General Mask!).  Kiting was nerfed slightly when the effectiveness of DoTs was dropped when a mob was not standing still/feared.  The list goes on.<P>Each time something gets nerfed, most members of that class grouse about it and then get on with finding a way around the nerf.  There's always a handful that asks that someone else's abilities should be nerfed in turn, as some sort of twisted compensation for their loss.  Is there any surprise that Bezze is getting roasted for basically asking that other people should be penalized even though they had nothing to do with his problem?<P>When you have broken eggs, you make omelets.  You don't ask that everyone else's eggs get smashed as well.  Asking for a nerf to another class because your own class suffered a nerf is poor gamesmanship.  And to paraphrase you, that's no opinion, that's a plain fact.
